"""
The TAF Pilot Light is a small application whose role is to enhance the availability of the test automation framework.
It checks the TAF server's capacity and allows, queues or rejects connection attempts and test execution requests.
An equally important function of the tool is process management, where it's ensured that if an incoming request arrives
at a time when the TAF server is down, (e.g. after the host machine is rebooted),
then it starts the necessary applications so the TAF can fulfill the request.
"""

One way to invoke the TAF is by copying a new AUT release into one of the preconfigured directories.
When a file is detected its SHA256 checksum is checked against the that of the previous releases 
and only installed if it is new. Depending on which directoy the file was detected in, 
the TAF may perform a full regression test, a smoke test, or installation only.

An alternative to using QFileSystemWatcher is inotify https://pypi.org/project/inotify/
"""
